    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-27T03:03:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-27T03:03:00-05:00" n="444"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/126: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">temporarily at Irkutsk, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Irkutsk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-27T15:00:00+06:57">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 27, 11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 20th, 11 a.m., reached me on my arrival at Irkutsk and I will
                    therefore remain here until receipt of the longer telegram referred to. Our
                    inability to send any additional troops as stated in your August 12th, 5 p.m.,
                    which I did not receive until August 23rd, in my judgment renders the entire
                    plan submitted in my August 11th impracticable. Under these circumstances I
                    think that any immediate recognition of <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> would be unwise as it would seem to promise more than we
                    can perform. It would be better to await <pb facs="0535" n="423" xml:id="pg_423"
                    /> the outcome of the present crisis when I will submit further suggestions for
                    the consideration of the Department after consulting <persName corresp="#p_SJF1"
                        >Stevens</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SCH1">Smith</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
